subSubSection.paragraph:
Descriptive notes.
Head-body length 110-140 mm, tail 135-175 mm, ear 8-14 mm, hindfoot 29-33 mm; weight 35-80 g (although most specimens are 35-50 g). The Lesser Treeshrew is the smallest tupaiid and looks remarkably similar to the Slender Treeshrew (7 
gracilis
). Fur of the Lesser Treeshrew is almost invariably light brown, with some subspecies having darker colored tails (particularly nominate 
minor
). Light brown color is nearly uniform across the body, and venteris ivory to tan. Tail is long. It has grasping feet and curved claws. Skulls is small, and rostrum is short. Shoulder marking is ivory and distinct.
